trans-unit.source: I finally figured out that you can't use optional swift types with setValue:forKey unless they have a direct mapping to an Objective-C type like String? or NSNumber?. I ended up changing all CShort? types to NSNumber? since that has a direct mapping. For Bool? in my case it was fine for me to just use Bool and initialize it to false. Others may not have that luxury.
trans-unit.target: 我终于弄清楚了，除非将可选的swift类型直接映射到诸如 String? 的Objective-C类型，否则不能将它们与 setValue:forKey 一起使用？ 还是 NSNumber? 。 我最终改变了所有 CShort? 类型为 NSNumber? 因为那有直接的映射 为了 Bool? 就我而言，只使用 Bool 并将其初始化为 false 是很好的。 其他人可能没有那么奢侈。

trans-unit.source: I had a similar problem for a project that has two targets (with their own MainWindow XIB). In creating a custom UITableViewCell using an XIB, I had mistakenly applied the Custom Class name to the File's Owner instead of to the UITableViewCell. Applying the class to the UITableViewCell on the canvas and connecting my IBOutlet properties to it solved the issue.
trans-unit.target: 我的解决方法和Gerard Grundy的方法类似。在使用 XIB 创建自定义 UITableViewCell 时,我错误地将自定义类名称应用到文件的所有者,而不是 UITableViewCell。将该类应用到画布上的UITableViewCell,并将我的IBOutlet属性连接到它,就解决了这个问题。
